{"TopicId":135064,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Alt function doesn\u0026#039;t work","CreatedByName":"SofusRud","CreatedById":59276,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T16:28:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SofusRud","CreatedById":59276,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T16:28:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a problem in that for some reason, the game doesn\u0027t register my use of the \u0022Alt\u0022 key, neither for bringing up the Debug menu or to duplicate parts in the editor. I have checked, and the key works fine on my other pc or when I\u0027m out of the game. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe functions of that key don\u0027t seem to be listed in the rebind section of the options menu, so I don\u0027t know how to rebind it. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m running the linux version on SteamOS. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease let me know what to do here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-27T17:55:09Z\u0022 title=\u002203/27/2016 05:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by SofusRud\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T18:20:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes your keyboard have an \u0022Fn\u0022 key?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it does you may have to use Fn\u002BAlt\u002BF12.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve heard others complaining about this, but haven\u0027t experienced it myself despite having an Fn key.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SofusRud","CreatedById":59276,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T20:30:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nno I don\u0027t think it does.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly\u00A0thing about the keyboard itself is that it\u0027s a danish keyboard, but that shouldn\u0027t affect the alt key\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kkUToq3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/kkUToq3.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-27T20:31:54Z\u0022 title=\u002203/27/2016 08:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by SofusRud\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Parv Kerman","CreatedById":160918,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T03:41:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat\u0027s an old keyboard. maybe that\u0027s why. replace your keboard from a new one. and if you wantto enable the debug window type fn\u002Balt\u002Bf12.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T05:18:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222475827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459096132\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259276\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SofusRud\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, SofusRud said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m running the linux version\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt becomes right-shift on the GNU/Linux build, as alt combos are often used by the window manager.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s no menu for it, but you can rebind if needed by editing the settings file.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-28T05:20:13Z\u0022 title=\u002203/28/2016 05:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SofusRud","CreatedById":59276,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T07:17:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459142325\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt becomes right-shift on the GNU/Linux build, as alt combos are often used by the window manager.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s no menu for it, but you can rebind if needed by editing the settings file.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there then no button on the linux version that does the \u0022duplicate part(s)\u0022 thing in the editor then?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Parv Kerman","CreatedById":160918,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T07:59:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nchange your operating system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SofusRud","CreatedById":59276,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T08:04:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459151982\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022parv kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, parv kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nchange your operating system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks, that\u0027s really not helpful at all. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T08:05:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459149432\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259276\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SofusRud\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, SofusRud said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there then no button on the linux version that does the \u0022duplicate part(s)\u0022 thing in the editor then?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nright-shift takes over alt, left shift as usual.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI don\u0027t immediately recall which key is duplicate in the editor (as I haven\u0027t played in a while), but it certainly worked for me a month or 2 ago (Debian 8) - I\u0027m pretty sure it\u0027s right-shift...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459136469\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022parv kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, parv kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nreplace your keboard from a new one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459151982\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022parv kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, parv kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nchange your operating system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, that\u0027s \u003Cem\u003Ereal\u003C/em\u003E helpful. Maybe the OP should replace the entire computer too?\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerhaps a different coloured chair would help? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459136469\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022parv kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, parv kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif you wantto enable the debug window type fn\u002Balt\u002Bf12.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you see an \u0027fn\u0027 key on the keyboard in that picture? no? Neither do I.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-28T08:11:20Z\u0022 title=\u002203/28/2016 08:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Parv Kerman","CreatedById":160918,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T08:07:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif it doesn\u0027t work I told you\u00A0 change your keyboard!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jansn67","CreatedById":158367,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T10:50:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteamOS is a Ubuntu derivat. You should check your Keyboard Settings and Button binding there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP Options i had to delete the binding to F12 (show temp gauges).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow ALT = right Shift (on my G15 blue)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}